<center>'''Level 346''' is the 347<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms.</center>

== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file= Level 346 Captured .png|caption=A well-known photograph of Level 346.}}
'''Level 346''' consists of a boundless sky filled with a perpectual light-blue fog. The only physical structures present within this space are large, solid spheres that drift slowly without any fixed direction. Despite the complete absence of gravity, these objects neither rise upward nor sink into the lower abyss. Instead, they remain locked on a single horizontal plane, continuously drifting through the central layer of the void.

Upon entry, one finds oneself directly standing on top of one of these spheres. Due to the immense scale of these structures, the surface appears flat beneath an individual’s feet. The curvature of the sphere only becomes apparent when one observe the distant horizon, where the surface gradually falls away into the surrounding blue haze. The spacing between spheres is extensive, resulting in large areas of empty space between each drifting structure. The air within the level is heavy and humid. Stepping off the edge of a sphere does not result in a fall; instead, one becomes completely stationary within the fog. Without a solid surface to exert force against, a stranded wanderer is unable to regain movement unless contacted by an another drifting sphere. All activity within the level is, therefore, dependent on the constant, unchanging velocity of these objects.

In the distance, multiple spheres occasionally cluster together, casting faint, elongated rays of shadow through the fog. They neither alter speed nor direction, instead continue their uniform drift through.<ref>The blue layer of the void, isolated from the empty regions above and below.</ref>



== Environmental Anomalies ==
* Stagnant Temperature: The ambient temperature within '''Level 346''' is constantly cold and completely still. There are no air currents, wind movements, or thermal exchanges. Active heat sources introduced by wanderers, such as flares or small fires, fail to warm the surrounding atmosphere. Thermal energy dissipates into the light-blue fog within a short radius without altering the general temperature of the air.

* Acoustic Dampening: Sound propagation in this environment is heavily muffled, especially near the surface of the spheres. Vocal communication is difficult and requires shouting to be understood even at close range. The solid material of the spheres absorbs the majority of mechanical vibrations upon impact, preventing echoes and creating an exceptionally quiet environment throughout the void.

* Synchronized Shifts: The drift of the spheres follows a structured pattern rather than a random course. At regular intervals twice a day, every sphere within the level simultaneously alters its horizontal path.<ref>This directional change occurs instantly without any felt kinetic vibration, magnetic fluctuations, or wind shifts, indicating a systemic movement.</ref>

== Psychological Hazards ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level 346 black balls.png|caption=Level 346, where the spheres turn black due to a human phenomenon.}}
Extended time within the endless blue haze severely distorts depth perception. The lack of clear reference points in the distance makes it difficult for the eyes to focus, often causing optical illusions related to space and scale. After hours in this environment, wanderers frequently feel as if they are shrinking or that the sphere beneath them is gradually expanding. This disruption in visual orientation often triggers a strong urge to lie flat on the ground, seeking stability against the vast, empty horizon.

Without gravity, profound psychological and sensory challenges arise. Visual confusion grows as trust in personal balance diminishes, because adherence to the surface relies solely on an unusual structural feature. When this becomes clear, severe spatial anxiety sets in, producing a false feeling of being pulled away by the surrounding void. As this anxiety builds, walking becomes increasingly difficult, with the mind convinced that detachment from the sphere is imminent.

Spending extended time in the level triggers intense visual hallucinations tied closely to a wanderer’s emotional state. As panic or severe anxiety sets in, nearby spheres begin to darken, progressively turning completely black as the distress intensifies. The more fear dominates, the larger these black spheres appear to the wanderer. Eventually, the growing darkness envelops their entire field of vision, causing a strong sensation of suffocation, despite the air remaining fully breathable.

The deep silence of the level intensifies the psychological strain. Faint, irregular vibrations are audible only when a wanderer presses their ear against the sphere’s matte surface. These low-frequency hums originate from deep within the structures’ cores. Over time, the sound appears to detach from the ground, becoming a persistent auditory hallucination in open air.<ref>This leads to ongoing disorientation as wanderers repeatedly turn, searching for a sound source along an empty horizon.</ref>

== Colonies and Outposts ==
There are no known colonies, outposts, or camps within '''Level 346'''. 

Establishing a permanent presence in this environment is considered impossible due to the severe psychological hazards caused by the endless blue void and the drifting spheres. The total lack of visual reference points leads to rapid spatial disorientation and mental exhaustion for any wanderer staying here.<ref>Additionally, the level contains zero natural resources; there is no supply of [[Object 1|Almond Water]], food, or salvageable materials available on the spheres, making long-term survival unfeasible.</ref>

== Addendum ==
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Addendum: "The Weight of the Blue Layer"</span>

I thought I was free of everything after escaping [[Level 345]], but what I found there was the exact opposite of emptiness.

There was no ground beneath me. No ceiling, no walls, no sensation of wind. Only a boundless open sky stretching indefinitely in every direction, painted in pale cyan and drowned with a dim turquoise haze. Distributed throughout the void were enormous turquoise spheres, each one smooth, are silent, and slowly drifting through the atmosphere like planets from [[The Frontrooms|our home reality itself]].

And I found myself sitting atop one of them; I was a living disturbance within the repettitive monotony. At first, I remained still. My body refused to move when as I stared downward at the sphere edge, my hands were shaking against its supernaturally freezing-cold surface. It was perfectly round; too perfect. There appeared neither cracks, nor texture. It resembled a polished ball of metal, yet it had a strange softness.

How could this be? I was supposed to be set free!

After every effects [[Level 345]] had affected to me; the auditory hallucinations, and the weeks I spent while doubting whether my own memories even belonged to me; I truly believed escaping it would finally end the torment. I expected it to be the way to safety, and expected myself being relieved afterwards. Instead, this place felt like a continuation of the punishment. Worse, perhaps. At least [[Level 345]] had walls; shelter.

Indifferent at all…

I laid on the surface of the sphere. My body was partially, and slightly bending with its curvature, yet, I felt somewhat flat and comfortable. For a long moment, I did nothing more but took rest and gaze at the drifting clusters of spheres above, while my mind creatively imagined them as spherical living beings having serious conversations with eachother. Although, the creations of my very own imagination appeared as if they were indirectly mocking my loneliness.

I suddenly jolted up. Not out of shock nor surprise; it was simply because of my sudden wave of curiosity. I started trying to step off of the sphere, but my fear of falling halted the effort. After many tries, I managed to step off. I realised it was not a good idea. I was statically floating and I was unable to move, while the sphere slowly drifted away from me.

I was just floating… while many spheres left me behind without colliding.

It became minutes, hours, or perhaps, days. It was not long until my fear started taking over. I started to panic as I might just be here forever. But then, in my terror, I watched as the turquoise spheres grew steadily blacker and larger, until I was completely engulfed by the blackness. I felt suffocated. There felt like air became non-existent. Then, I somehow lost consciousness.

I do not exactly remember what really happened right there.

When I opened my eyes, [[Level 6|there was still darkness]].

<div style="text-align: right;">– ''Recovered Wanderer Journal (Identity Unknown)''</div>

</div>

== Entrances & Exits ==

=== Entrances ===
* Touching a small, round turquoise toy ball toy replica of a wireframe sphere found within the residential buildings of [[Level 345]] will cause an immediate transition to this level.
* In the commercial structures of [[Level 365]], certain windows occasionally display a glitching, pale-blue sky filled with drifting spherical shapes instead of the regular outside view. Stepping through these windows will deposit a wanderer onto the surface of a sphere in Level 346.
* Noclipping through a corrupted, glowing blue texture on the walls of [[Level 4]] has a rare chance of dropping a wanderer directly into the heavy fog of this environment.

* Noclipping through a dark mossy wall in [[Level 8]] will lead you directly here.

=== Exits ===
* If a wanderer waits on the edge of a sphere until it collides with another, the brief geometric warp creates a localized glitch. Stepping into this distorted wireframe grid will safely return the wanderer back to the entrance point in [[Level 345]].
* Jumping off a sphere and drifting into the lower, darker layer of the abyss for a prolonged period will eventually cause the wanderer to lose consciousness, waking up in the dark corridors of [[Level 6]].
* Locating a rare sphere whose wireframe grid has turned completely black and solid allows a wanderer to clip through its center, leading directly into [[Level 233]].

